Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.55,0:00:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The most precious moment in life
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.16,0:00:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is the time of decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.50,0:00:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.58,0:00:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ketsudan (decision)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.88,0:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your wisdom, Use your head Keep thinking if you're a man
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you cry or laugh, it depends on your decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be arrogant even if you win Don't cry even if you lose
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.16,0:01:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Man does not show tears
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.52,0:01:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tatsunoko Production
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.92,0:01:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In May 1942, the Kokoda Track Campaign, aimed at securing a base in Rabaul and controlling northern Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.70,0:01:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,began with the capture of Tulagi Island by a special land force that assaulted the port of Rabaul.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.46,0:01:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:02:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Australian Reserve, who knew in advance of the Japanese attack, had already withdrawn and the port was empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.66,0:02:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At 6:30 a.m. on May 4th, Major General Fletcher, the commander off the US Mobile Task Force, who learned of the Japanese occupation of Tulagi Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.34,0:02:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately sortied his aircraft from the carrier Lexington, and launched an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.85,0:02:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of the Coral Sea (Episode Eight)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.34,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the Japanese side was waiting for a report from the front line, with Commander-in-Chief of the 4th Fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Inoue, taking overall command of Rabaul Island Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.62,0:03:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.66,0:03:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,One destroyer, two minesweepers, and one submarine chaser sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.24,0:03:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that carrier-based aircraft have attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.84,0:03:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,means that the US Navy has advanced into the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.20,0:03:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.16,0:03:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy task force must be within 200 nautical miles of Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.84,0:03:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,However, our task force is currently refueling about 360 nautical miles north of Tulagi Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.44,0:03:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the enemy knows the movement of our navy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.78,0:03:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but that is besides the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.81,0:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Since they know that the purpose of our navy's operation is Port Morseby,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.96,0:04:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy will not be able to move from the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.90,0:04:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Telegram from the Chief of the Combined Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We are pleased to be able to destroy the US aircraft carriers that we have been struggling with since the beginning of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,On May 6, the Japanese Navy Mobile Task Force, under the command of Major General Takeo Takagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.70,0:04:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced into the Coral Sea in response to the order to destroy the US Mobile Task Force.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.16,0:04:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Takagi, Commander of the 5th Carrier Division, and Major General Hara were staring out from the bridge Of the Japanese Navy's escort aircraft carrier Zuikaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.94,0:04:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we find it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.92,0:04:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm afraid of too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.94,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow night, we will pass through the southern tip of San Cristobal Island
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.10,0:04:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and enter the Coral Sea from the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.24,0:04:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like looking for a loach in the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the US Mobile Task Force, whose flagships were the two aircraft carriers Yorktown and Lexington,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.92,0:05:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,was gathering together with the Combined Fleet of the United Kingdom and Australia, about 360 nautical miles south of Guadalcanal Island, to meet the Japanese fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Fletcher, commander of the US MTF, held an operational meeting on the aircraft carrier Yorktown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan's Kokoda Track Campaign is expected to pass through the Solomon Sea on the 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So what about the Japanese MTF?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no doubt that they are heading south on the west side of the Solomon Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but their exact location is not yet known.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.38,0:05:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyways, discover the aircraft carriers before the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As quick as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.74,0:06:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A battle between carriers is decided by a momentary difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.32,0:06:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the Japanese and US troops were desperately searching for an opponent to launch a first strike on,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.00,0:06:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but nothing happened during the two days of May 5th and 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.38,0:06:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the enemy's aim to strike us tomorrow, when our troops pass through the Solomon Sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.14,0:06:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, maybe their aim is the day after tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when we are heading for Port Moresby on the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.68,0:06:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is the day after tomorrow, they will probably act around the south tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.82,0:06:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is like hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the one who finds the enemy first wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to catch and destroy the enemy tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What if there are no enemies at the estimated position?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we also head west to the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, the Japanese convoy carrying the Port Moresby assault units were protected by an escort centered on the carrier Shoho.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.50,0:07:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They were moving southward in the central part of the Solomon Sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.96,0:07:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but after 9 a.m., it was wary because the enemy aircraft were close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew. Man your stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.30,0:07:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one enemy aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.81,0:07:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Track it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.70,0:07:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, for the first time in history, a battle between aircraft carriers was gradually approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.54,0:07:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy aircraft carriers are always near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.18,0:07:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for the enemy with great care so as not to betray our radio wave detection.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.20,0:07:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from the reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.56,0:08:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Discovered an enemy aircraft carrier. 400 nautical miles southwest of Tulagi Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.88,0:08:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ship attack, ship bombing, all aircraft take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.68,0:08:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese side, at the Rabaul Island base
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.94,0:08:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is at Rossel Island at 170°, 82 nautical miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We observed that the enemy task force is split in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,First, attack the enemy troops in the direction of Rossel Island with all our might,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,while the convoy evacuates to the northwest under the escort of the MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.70,0:08:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.52,0:08:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the 5th Carrier Division is already 400 nautical miles southwest of Tulagi,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.12,0:09:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and has begun a full-scale attack on the enemy aircraft carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.06,0:09:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a refueling ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the carriers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.28,0:10:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The carriers!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.08,0:10:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Around this time, the Japanese side had a convoy escort aircraft carrier Shoho,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,under attack by carrier-based aircraft of the US MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. She was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.48,0:11:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.44,0:11:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the responsibility of the 5th Carrier Division for the loss of Shoho.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it possible to mistake a refueling ship and a carrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.24,0:12:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, everyone is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.60,0:12:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, communications staff?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw away the bombs and torpedoes and recall them right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At this pace, we can't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.02,0:12:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming that the returning attacking unit is hurriedly collected,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.28,0:12:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,our MTF will pursue and destroy the enemy in the northwest at full speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Be sure to take revenge on Shoho's behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.46,0:13:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we have wasted too much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.70,0:13:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.60,0:13:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A night attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.56,0:13:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The 5th Carrier Division has excellent pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.32,0:13:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was no wonder that the Japanese commander was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.34,0:13:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The 5th Carrier Division was formed just before the start of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pilot training was insufficient, especially at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.26,0:14:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Major General Hara, the commander of the 5th Carrier Division, forcibly ignored it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.90,0:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do it seriously, we can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, if the commander says as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.06,0:14:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Order:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The main unit will attack the enemy task force in the north of the Coral Sea at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.52,0:14:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship has excellent pilots, organize six carrier-capable bombers and nine carrier-capable attack aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and launch promptly as soon as it is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.28,0:14:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a deadly attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.12,0:15:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese aircraft are unaware of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.46,0:15:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The goddess of victory is smiling at our MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.26,0:15:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Attack immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.52,0:15:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The North is squalid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.42,0:15:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, upper right sky, enemy planes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.76,0:15:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.66,0:15:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they find us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.40,0:15:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw away all torpedoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.06,0:15:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They are relieved because there are no fighters on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Find that carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it's near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.08,0:16:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.66,0:16:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from the 5th Carrier Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.06,0:16:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't found the carriers and I am being attacked by the enemy's fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.58,0:16:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I am engaged with enemy fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.90,0:16:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My unit is annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. Where did my home go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.44,0:16:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,l want to go home early and take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.30,0:16:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, we will have to take a ridiculously large bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.26,0:16:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, it's a cold bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.22,0:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A friendly carrier was spotted 60° to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.42,0:16:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:16:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately move to landing mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.66,0:17:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.70,0:17:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an enemy carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The numbers on the deck and the shape of the bridge are different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.74,0:17:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.48,0:17:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They are back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:17:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.46,0:17:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an enemy carrier right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.10,0:18:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.02,0:18:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Other pilots also saw it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.06,0:18:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Night attacks are difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.02,0:18:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How about tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.80,0:18:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The second day of the Battle of the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.06,0:18:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The US and Japanese troops, who could not wait for dawn, launched reconnaissance aircraft in search of the others carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.10,0:18:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an enemy carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.76,0:18:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from the reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.26,0:18:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I found an enemy carrier, I'm approaching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.20,0:18:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,205° from our allied position, 235 nautical miles. Course 170°, speed 16 knots
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.80,0:19:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Two aircraft carriers, one battleship, two cruisers, one light cruiser, and six destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. We only have fuel for the return trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.06,0:19:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We've reported this in detail, so it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.00,0:19:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.12,0:19:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I will stop approaching the enemy and return.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.78,0:19:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost at the same time, the US reconnaissance aircraft also discovered the Japanese MTF.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather is changing quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to accurately guide our allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.96,0:20:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from the reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I will stop returning and guide my allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.62,0:20:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave it to you, the attacking unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.82,0:20:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.54,0:20:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our fuel has run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.40,0:21:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.52,0:21:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Full starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.68,0:21:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.36,0:21:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exactly the wind of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.82,0:21:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.98,0:21:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Shokaku is taking on the enemy at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.96,0:22:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was badly done.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.46,0:22:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.76,0:22:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After the battle was over, the aircraft carrier Zuikaku appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.06,0:22:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Communication staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Report to Rabaul’s Fleet Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.86,0:22:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The attacking force is returning around 11 a.m., and the troops are being prepared, but today there is no prospect of a second attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.56,0:22:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, because of the munitions and fuel consumed, high-speed navigation at night is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.80,0:22:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander Inoue of the 4th fleet received the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.84,0:22:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped if Shokaku was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.00,0:22:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the attack and order it to go north.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.24,0:22:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Port Moresby has been postponed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.56,0:22:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Was Operation Port Moresby postponed?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.90,0:23:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's issue a pursuit order.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.02,0:23:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The MTF of the 4th Fleet, which was ordered by the Chief of the Combined Fleet, Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.00,0:23:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,went south at full speed at 2:00 a.m. on the 9th,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.94,0:23:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but could no longer capture the US MITE.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon hearing this report, the Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto immediately removed the MTF from the 4th Fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.88,0:23:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This was because the day of the next scheduled operation, Midway, was approaching, but at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.34,0:23:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he was dissatisfied with the commander who abandoned the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.04,0:23:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The damage caused by this naval battle was almost the same on both the Japanese and US side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.44,0:23:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When you are too caught up in the damage of your allies, the damage to the enemy is overlooked and the operation stagnates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.28,0:23:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The 4th Fleet of the Japanese Navy won tactically,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.78,0:23:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but lost the overall strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.72,0:24:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace, but it also leaves us with many lessons to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.61,0:24:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Java (Episode Nine)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, test your strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.50,0:24:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, burn your hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.88,0:24:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a man, don't let yourself down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I and you are men and men bleed the same bright red blood.
